    "23465069": {
      "title": "A Reliable Method for Disseminating Safety Information in Vehicular Ad Hoc Networks Considering Fragmentation Problem",
      "abstract": "Many of applications in vehicular ad hoc networks (VANET) are based on dissemination of information, so broadcasting is a fundamental service in these networks. Broadcasting is a difficult task since vehicular networks often lack continuous end-to-end connectivity and have large variations in node densities. In this paper we present a method that improves the reception rates of broadcast messages by overcoming problem of connectivity gaps. In our method, every forwarder of message when facing a gap sends small messages periodically. These methods are used to understand entrance of a new vehicle that can be selected as the next forwarder of message. We have evaluated the performance of proposed protocol in NS2 under various network conditions."
